{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1015,"text":"What do you think when you look at me?"},{"time":4000,"text":"A woman of faith? An expert?"},{"time":7145,"text":"Maybe even a sister."},{"time":9391,"text":"Or oppressed,"},{"time":11702,"text":"brainwashed,"},{"time":13237,"text":"a terrorist."},{"time":16061,"text":"Or just an airport security line delay."},{"time":20571,"text":"That one's actually true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22104,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":23684,"text":"If some of your perceptions were negative,\nI don't really blame you."},{"time":26931,"text":"That's just how the media\nhas been portraying"},{"time":29075,"text":"people who look like me."},{"time":30629,"text":"One study found"},{"time":32059,"text":"that 80 percent of news coverage\nabout Islam and Muslims is negative."},{"time":36828,"text":"And studies show that Americans\nsay that most don't know a Muslim."},{"time":41088,"text":"I guess people don't talk\nto their Uber drivers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43968,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":47365,"text":"Well, for those of you\nwho have never met a Muslim,"},{"time":50988,"text":"it's great to meet you."},{"time":53738,"text":"Let me tell you who I am."},{"time":56731,"text":"I'm a mom, a coffee lover --"},{"time":59858,"text":"double espresso, cream on the side."},{"time":62103,"text":"I'm an introvert."},{"time":64089,"text":"I'm a wannabe fitness fanatic."},{"time":66120,"text":"And I'm a practicing, spiritual Muslim."},{"time":71788,"text":"But not like Lady Gaga says,\nbecause baby, I wasn't born this way."},{"time":76931,"text":"It was a choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79640,"text":"When I was 17, I decided to come out."},{"time":83679,"text":"No, not as a gay person\nlike some of my friends,"},{"time":86864,"text":"but as a Muslim,"},{"time":88388,"text":"and decided to start wearing\nthe hijab, my head covering."},{"time":92216,"text":"My feminist friends were aghast:"},{"time":95771,"text":"\"Why are you oppressing yourself?\""},{"time":99436,"text":"The funny thing was,"},{"time":100992,"text":"it was actually at that time\na feminist declaration of independence"},{"time":106898,"text":"from the pressure I felt as a 17-year-old,"},{"time":110880,"text":"to conform to a perfect\nand unattainable standard of beauty."},{"time":115582,"text":"I didn't just passively accept\nthe faith of my parents."},{"time":120658,"text":"I wrestled with the Quran."},{"time":122888,"text":"I read and reflected\nand questioned and doubted"},{"time":128428,"text":"and, ultimately, believed."},{"time":131621,"text":"My relationship with God --\nit was not love at first sight."},{"time":137614,"text":"It was a trust and a slow surrender"},{"time":140512,"text":"that deepened with every\nreading of the Quran."},{"time":144133,"text":"Its rhythmic beauty\nsometimes moves me to tears."},{"time":148909,"text":"I see myself in it.\nI feel that God knows me."},{"time":153069,"text":"Have you ever felt like someone sees you,\ncompletely understands you"},{"time":158685,"text":"and yet loves you anyway?"},{"time":160923,"text":"That's how it feels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163773,"text":"And so later, I got married,"},{"time":166477,"text":"and like all good Egyptians,"},{"time":168365,"text":"started my career as an engineer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170848,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":174602,"text":"I later had a child,\nafter getting married,"},{"time":179603,"text":"and I was living essentially\nthe Egyptian-American dream."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186448,"text":"And then that terrible morning\nof September, 2001."},{"time":192417,"text":"I think a lot of you probably remember\nexactly where you were that morning."},{"time":199181,"text":"I was sitting in my kitchen\nfinishing breakfast,"},{"time":202912,"text":"and I look up on the screen\nand see the words \"Breaking News.\""},{"time":207075,"text":"There was smoke,\nairplanes flying into buildings,"},{"time":210490,"text":"people jumping out of buildings."},{"time":213277,"text":"What was this?"},{"time":215456,"text":"An accident?"},{"time":217786,"text":"A malfunction?"},{"time":221084,"text":"My shock quickly turned to outrage."},{"time":224550,"text":"Who would do this?"},{"time":227385,"text":"And I switch the channel and I hear,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":230111,"text":"\"... Muslim terrorist ...,\""},{"time":232191,"text":"\"... in the name of Islam ...,\""},{"time":234212,"text":"\"... Middle-Eastern descent ...,\""},{"time":236585,"text":"\"... jihad ...,\""},{"time":238420,"text":"\"... we should bomb Mecca.\""},{"time":240294,"text":"Oh my God."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243232,"text":"Not only had my country been attacked,"},{"time":247080,"text":"but in a flash,"},{"time":248446,"text":"somebody else's actions\nhad turned me from a citizen"},{"time":252376,"text":"to a suspect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255021,"text":"That same day, we had to drive\nacross Middle America"},{"time":259982,"text":"to move to a new city\nto start grad school."},{"time":264908,"text":"And I remember sitting\nin the passenger seat"},{"time":267015,"text":"as we drove in silence,"},{"time":269871,"text":"crouched as low as I could go in my seat,"},{"time":272481,"text":"for the first time in my life,\nafraid for anyone to know I was a Muslim."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278943,"text":"We moved into our apartment\nthat night in a new town"},{"time":282110,"text":"in what felt like\na completely different world."},{"time":285928,"text":"And then I was hearing\nand seeing and reading"},{"time":289906,"text":"warnings from national\nMuslim organizations"},{"time":292627,"text":"saying things like,\n\"Be alert,\" \"Be aware,\""},{"time":296312,"text":"\"Stay in well-lit areas,\"\n\"Don't congregate.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":300180,"text":"I stayed inside all week."},{"time":302988,"text":"And then it was Friday that same week,"},{"time":305756,"text":"the day that Muslims\ncongregate for worship."},{"time":310035,"text":"And again the warnings were,\n\"Don't go that first Friday,"},{"time":314625,"text":"it could be a target.\""},{"time":317512,"text":"And I was watching the news,\nwall-to-wall coverage."},{"time":320187,"text":"Emotions were so raw, understandably,"},{"time":323076,"text":"and I was also hearing\nabout attacks on Muslims,"},{"time":326778,"text":"or people who were perceived\nto be Muslim, being pulled out"},{"time":329620,"text":"and beaten in the street."},{"time":330866,"text":"Mosques were actually firebombed."},{"time":333004,"text":"And I thought, we should just stay home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":335777,"text":"And yet, something didn't feel right."},{"time":339335,"text":"Because those people\nwho attacked our country"},{"time":341792,"text":"attacked our country."},{"time":346611,"text":"I get it that people were angry\nat the terrorists."},{"time":349441,"text":"Guess what? So was I."},{"time":352897,"text":"And so to have to explain yourself\nall the time isn't easy."},{"time":358193,"text":"I don't mind questions. I love questions."},{"time":361582,"text":"It's the accusations that are tough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364583,"text":"Today we hear people actually\nsaying things like,"},{"time":368278,"text":"\"There's a problem in this country,\nand it's called Muslims."},{"time":371108,"text":"When are we going to get rid of them?\""},{"time":373504,"text":"So, some people want to ban Muslims\nand close down mosques."},{"time":377197,"text":"They talk about my community\nkind of like we're a tumor"},{"time":380279,"text":"in the body of America."},{"time":381944,"text":"And the only question is,\nare we malignant or benign?"},{"time":385866,"text":"You know, a malignant tumor\nyou extract altogether,"},{"time":388871,"text":"and a benign tumor\nyou just keep under surveillance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395467,"text":"The choices don't make sense,\nbecause it's the wrong question."},{"time":399893,"text":"Muslims, like all other Americans,\naren't a tumor in the body of America,"},{"time":403818,"text":"we're a vital organ."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406109,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":407134,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408317,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":413937,"text":"Muslims are inventors and teachers,"},{"time":416527,"text":"first responders and Olympic athletes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420341,"text":"Now, is closing down mosques\ngoing to make America safer?"},{"time":424194,"text":"It might free up some parking spots,"},{"time":427294,"text":"but it will not end terrorism."},{"time":430134,"text":"Going to a mosque regularly\nis actually linked"},{"time":432611,"text":"to having more tolerant views\nof people of other faiths"},{"time":436541,"text":"and greater civic engagement."},{"time":439561,"text":"And as one police chief\nin the Washington, DC area"},{"time":442866,"text":"recently told me,"},{"time":444041,"text":"people don't actually\nget radicalized at mosques."},{"time":446925,"text":"They get radicalized in their basement\nor bedroom, in front of a computer."},{"time":452526,"text":"And what you find\nabout the radicalization process"},{"time":455380,"text":"is it starts online,"},{"time":457027,"text":"but the first thing that happens"},{"time":458622,"text":"is the person gets cut off\nfrom their community,"},{"time":461640,"text":"from even their family,"},{"time":463306,"text":"so that the extremist group\ncan brainwash them"},{"time":466098,"text":"into believing that they,\nthe terrorists, are the true Muslims,"},{"time":470420,"text":"and everyone else who abhors\ntheir behavior and ideology"},{"time":474460,"text":"are sellouts or apostates."},{"time":477607,"text":"So if we want to prevent radicalization,"},{"time":479886,"text":"we have to keep people\ngoing to the mosque."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484765,"text":"Now, some will still argue\nIslam is a violent religion."},{"time":488517,"text":"After all, a group like ISIS\nbases its brutality on the Quran."},{"time":494318,"text":"Now, as a Muslim, as a mother,\nas a human being,"},{"time":497676,"text":"I think we need to do everything we can\nto stop a group like ISIS."},{"time":503720,"text":"But we would be giving in\nto their narrative"},{"time":508624,"text":"if we cast them as representatives\nof a faith of 1.6 billion people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514373,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":517890,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521809,"text":"ISIS has as much to do with Islam"},{"time":525117,"text":"as the Ku Klux Klan has to do\nwith Christianity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528491,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":534795,"text":"Both groups claim to base\ntheir ideology on their holy book."},{"time":540349,"text":"But when you look at them,\nthey're not motivated"},{"time":543397,"text":"by what they read in their holy book."},{"time":545705,"text":"It's their brutality that makes them\nread these things into the scripture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552098,"text":"Recently, a prominent imam\ntold me a story that really took me aback."},{"time":555772,"text":"He said that a girl came to him"},{"time":557535,"text":"because she was thinking\nof going to join ISIS."},{"time":560556,"text":"And I was really surprised and asked him,"},{"time":562628,"text":"had she been in contact\nwith a radical religious leader?"},{"time":565898,"text":"And he said the problem\nwas quite the opposite,"},{"time":568217,"text":"that every cleric that she had\ntalked to had shut her down"},{"time":571968,"text":"and said that her rage,\nher sense of injustice in the world,"},{"time":575589,"text":"was just going to get her in trouble."},{"time":577698,"text":"And so with nowhere to channel\nand make sense of this anger,"},{"time":581403,"text":"she was a prime target to be exploited"},{"time":583442,"text":"by extremists promising her a solution."},{"time":586605,"text":"What this imam did was to connect her\nback to God and to her community."},{"time":591319,"text":"He didn't shame her for her rage --\ninstead, he gave her constructive ways"},{"time":596190,"text":"to make real change in the world."},{"time":598751,"text":"What she learned at that mosque\nprevented her from going to join ISIS."}]},{"cues":[{"time":604983,"text":"I've told you a little bit"},{"time":606262,"text":"about how Islamophobia\naffects me and my family."},{"time":609076,"text":"But how does it impact ordinary Americans?"},{"time":611640,"text":"How does it impact everyone else?"},{"time":613569,"text":"How does consuming fear 24 hours a day\naffect the health of our democracy,"},{"time":619359,"text":"the health of our free thought?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":621527,"text":"Well, one study -- actually,\nseveral studies in neuroscience --"},{"time":625422,"text":"show that when we're afraid,\nat least three things happen."},{"time":629857,"text":"We become more accepting\nof authoritarianism,"},{"time":634002,"text":"conformity and prejudice."},{"time":637194,"text":"One study showed that when subjects\nwere exposed to news stories"},{"time":643005,"text":"that were negative about Muslims,"},{"time":646013,"text":"they became more accepting\nof military attacks on Muslim countries"},{"time":650152,"text":"and policies that curtail the rights\nof American Muslims."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654192,"text":"Now, this isn't just academic."},{"time":656373,"text":"When you look at when\nanti-Muslim sentiment spiked"},{"time":661555,"text":"between 2001 and 2013,"},{"time":665127,"text":"it happened three times,"},{"time":666718,"text":"but it wasn't around terrorist attacks."},{"time":669294,"text":"It was in the run up to the Iraq War\nand during two election cycles."},{"time":674155,"text":"So Islamophobia isn't just\nthe natural response to Muslim terrorism"},{"time":678723,"text":"as I would have expected."},{"time":681218,"text":"It can actually be a tool\nof public manipulation,"},{"time":685720,"text":"eroding the very foundation\nof a free society,"},{"time":689727,"text":"which is rational\nand well-informed citizens."},{"time":694605,"text":"Muslims are like canaries\nin the coal mine."},{"time":697655,"text":"We might be the first to feel it,"},{"time":699370,"text":"but the toxic air of fear\nis harming us all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704251,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":711580,"text":"And assigning collective guilt"},{"time":714003,"text":"isn't just about having\nto explain yourself all the time."},{"time":717777,"text":"Deah and his wife Yusor\nwere a young married couple"},{"time":721449,"text":"living in Chapel Hill, North Carolina,"},{"time":723472,"text":"where they both went to school."},{"time":725686,"text":"Deah was an athlete."},{"time":728125,"text":"He was in dental school,\ntalented, promising ..."},{"time":732260,"text":"And his sister would tell me\nthat he was the sweetest,"},{"time":736502,"text":"most generous human being she knew."},{"time":738561,"text":"She was visiting him there\nand he showed her his resume,"},{"time":742439,"text":"and she was amazed."},{"time":743725,"text":"She said, \"When did my baby brother\nbecome such an accomplished young man?\""},{"time":749119,"text":"Just a few weeks after Suzanne's visit\nto her brother and his new wife,"},{"time":754237,"text":"their neighbor,"},{"time":756732,"text":"Craig Stephen Hicks,"},{"time":758897,"text":"murdered them,"},{"time":760666,"text":"as well as Yusor's sister, Razan,\nwho was visiting for the afternoon,"},{"time":765471,"text":"in their apartment,"},{"time":767754,"text":"execution style,"},{"time":769533,"text":"after posting anti-Muslim statements\non his Facebook page."},{"time":774058,"text":"He shot Deah eight times."},{"time":777254,"text":"So bigotry isn't just immoral,\nit can even be lethal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":782355,"text":"So, back to my story."},{"time":783700,"text":"What happened after 9/11?"},{"time":785424,"text":"Did we go to the mosque\nor did we play it safe and stay home?"},{"time":789390,"text":"Well, we talked it over,"},{"time":791296,"text":"and it might seem like\na small decision, but to us,"},{"time":794009,"text":"it was about what kind of America\nwe wanted to leave for our kids:"},{"time":797889,"text":"one that would control us by fear"},{"time":801293,"text":"or one where we were practicing\nour religion freely."},{"time":804811,"text":"So we decided to go to the mosque."},{"time":807823,"text":"And we put my son in his car seat,"},{"time":809590,"text":"buckled him in, and we drove silently,\nintensely, to the mosque."},{"time":813305,"text":"I took him out, I took off my shoes,\nI walked into the prayer hall"},{"time":818609,"text":"and what I saw made me stop."},{"time":821271,"text":"The place was completely full."},{"time":823492,"text":"And then the imam made an announcement,"},{"time":825704,"text":"thanking and welcoming our guests,"},{"time":830564,"text":"because half the congregation"},{"time":833833,"text":"were Christians, Jews,\nBuddhists, atheists,"},{"time":836585,"text":"people of faith and no faith,"},{"time":839029,"text":"who had come not to attack us,\nbut to stand in solidarity with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844419,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":853599,"text":"I just break down at this time."},{"time":856674,"text":"These people were there because they chose\ncourage and compassion"},{"time":861242,"text":"over panic and prejudice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864731,"text":"What will you choose?"},{"time":867122,"text":"What will you choose\nat this time of fear and bigotry?"},{"time":873397,"text":"Will you play it safe?"},{"time":875914,"text":"Or will you join those who say"},{"time":878237,"text":"we are better than that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":880249,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881424,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":895910,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":900497,"text":"Helen Walters: So Dalia,\nyou seem to have struck a chord."},{"time":904865,"text":"But I wonder,"},{"time":906426,"text":"what would you say to those\nwho might argue"},{"time":908909,"text":"that you're giving a TED Talk,"},{"time":910690,"text":"you're clearly a deep thinker,"},{"time":912269,"text":"you work at a fancy think tank,"},{"time":914300,"text":"you're an exception, you're not the rule."},{"time":916437,"text":"What would you say to those people?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":918841,"text":"Dalia Mogahed: I would say,\ndon't let this stage distract you,"},{"time":921787,"text":"I'm completely ordinary."},{"time":923821,"text":"I'm not an exception."},{"time":925447,"text":"My story is not unusual."},{"time":927491,"text":"I am as ordinary as they come."},{"time":930498,"text":"When you look at Muslims\naround the world --"},{"time":934720,"text":"and I've done this, I've done\nthe largest study ever done"},{"time":937575,"text":"on Muslims around the world --"},{"time":939141,"text":"people want ordinary things."},{"time":940615,"text":"They want prosperity for their family,"},{"time":942464,"text":"they want jobs"},{"time":943639,"text":"and they want to live in peace."},{"time":945269,"text":"So I am not in any way an exception."},{"time":948339,"text":"When you meet people who seem\nlike an exception to the rule,"},{"time":951214,"text":"oftentimes it's that the rule is broken,"},{"time":954292,"text":"not that they're an exception to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":956536,"text":"HW: Thank you so much.\nDalia Mogahed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":959020,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}